FBIS4-8640 "dreeu073_y_94011" FBIS-EEU-94-073 Daily Report 14 Apr 1994 YUGOSLAVIA Serbia Owen: NATO Actions Against Serbs Justified Owen: NATO Actions Against Serbs Justified LD1404194294 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service in Serbo-Croatian 1840 GMT 14 Apr 94 LD1404194294 Belgrade TANJUG Domestic Service Serbo-Croatian BFN [Text] Belgrade, 14 Apr (TANJUG)--David Owen, cochairman of the Conference on the Former Yugoslavia, told journalists this evening before his talks with Serbian President Slobodan Milosevic that NATO air attacks near Gorazde were justified, basing his explanation on UN Security Council resolutions. He categorically rejected claims that the United Nations had placed itself on the side of the Muslims, stressing that it was now most important to restore the peace process and resume dialogue between the sides in the conflict.
